# ── Sanity CMS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The LIVE Finaccru project id is already baked into sanity/env.ts as the
# default (id "2jhreob8", dataset "production"), so the CMS works out of the box
# with NO .env. These are PUBLIC values (they appear in every Sanity CDN URL),
# which is why hard-coding the default is safe.
#
# Create a `.env` from this file ONLY to point at a different project/dataset
# (e.g. a "staging" dataset) without editing source. The VITE_ prefix exposes
# them to the browser/Studio build, which is fine for these public values.
#
# VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=2jhreob8
# VITE_SANITY_DATASET=production
# VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2024-12-01

# Only needed if you make the dataset PRIVATE (then also add `token` in
# sanity/lib/client.ts). Keep this out of version control — it is a secret.
# SANITY_READ_TOKEN=

# ── Contact form / SMTP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The contact form (src/lib/contact.server.ts → email.ts) sends mail over SMTP
# from inside the Cloudflare Worker. The PUBLIC config (SMTP_HOST / SMTP_PORT /
# SMTP_USER / ADMIN_EMAILS) lives in wrangler.jsonc `vars`; only the password is
# secret. In production set it once with:
#   wrangler secret put SMTP_PASSWORD
#
# For local `vite dev` / `wrangler dev`, create a `.dev.vars` file (gitignored,
# same KEY=VALUE format) with at least the password — and override any of the
# public vars there if your local SMTP differs:
#   SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
#   # SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
#   # SMTP_PORT=465
#   # SMTP_USER=hello@finaccru.com
#   # ADMIN_EMAILS=hello@finaccru.com
